Quid dicam? O. Vergilio, tali civi et viro, benevolentiam in me, memoriam communium temporum, pietatem, humanitatem, fidem defuisse? When Cicero left Rome he intended to visit Sicily, where he expected a welcome reception. He does not say where he re- ceived notice that Vergilius would not allow him to enter his province. He makes his reason for leaving Vibo all at once to be Vergilius’ refusa13 but in the letter to Atti- cus he states another reason.
